The paper focuses on optimizing graph reachability queries on databases, which is a core topic in database management systems (cs.DB). The use of aggregation on single output attribute and the biomedical field also suggest a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also introduces a new form of query processing execution strategy and data organization, which are relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of compiled code and space-time tradeoff, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE).
